Iterable
   ↓
Collection
   ├── List
   │     ├── ArrayList
   │     │     [Insertion Order Preserved |
   │     │      Duplicates Allowed |
   │     │      Non-Synchronized |
   │     │      Backed by Dynamic Array |
   │     │      Best for Read/Random Access O(1)]
   │
   │     ├── LinkedList
   │     │     [Insertion Order Preserved |
   │     │      Duplicates Allowed |
   │     │      Non-Synchronized |
   │     │      Doubly Linked List |
   │     │      Best for Frequent Add/Remove Operations]
   │
   │     └── Vector
   │           [Insertion Order Preserved |
   │            Duplicates Allowed |
   │            Synchronized |
   │            Legacy Class |
   │            Slower due to Synchronization]
   │
   ├── Set
   │     ├── HashSet
   │     │     [No Insertion Order Guarantee |
   │     │      Duplicates Not Allowed |
   │     │      Allows One NULL |
   │     │      Non-Synchronized |
   │     │      Internally uses HashMap |
   │     │      Average O(1) operations]
   │
   │     ├── LinkedHashSet
   │     │     [Insertion Order Preserved |
   │     │      Duplicates Not Allowed |
   │     │      Non-Synchronized |
   │     │      Uses HashTable + Linked List |
   │     │      Slightly slower than HashSet]
   │
   │     └── TreeSet
   │           [Sorted Order (Natural / Comparator) |
   │            Duplicates Not Allowed |
   │            Non-Synchronized |
   │            Based on Red-Black Tree |
   │            O(log n) operations |
   │            NULL Not Allowed]
   │
   └── Queue
         ├── PriorityQueue
         │     [Elements Ordered by Priority |
         │      Not FIFO |
         │      Duplicates Allowed |
         │      Non-Synchronized |
         │      Heap Data Structure |
         │      Head = Highest Priority Element]
         │
         └── Deque
                └── ArrayDeque
                      [Insertion Order Maintained |
                       Duplicates Allowed |
                       Non-Synchronized |
                       Faster than Stack & LinkedList |
                       Supports FIFO and LIFO operations]

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Map
   ├── HashMap
   │     [No Ordering Guarantee |
   │      One NULL Key Allowed |
   │      Duplicate Keys Not Allowed |
   │      Non-Synchronized |
   │      Based on Hashing |
   │      Average O(1) retrieval]
   │
   ├── LinkedHashMap
   │     [Insertion Order Preserved |
   │      Duplicate Keys Not Allowed |
   │      Non-Synchronized |
   │      HashMap + Doubly Linked List |
   │      Used for LRU Cache implementations]
   │
   ├── TreeMap
   │     [Sorted by Natural Order / Comparator |
   │      Duplicate Keys Not Allowed |
   │      Non-Synchronized |
   │      Red-Black Tree |
   │      O(log n) operations |
   │      NULL Key Not Allowed]
   │
   └── Hashtable
         [No NULL Key or Value |
          Synchronized |
          Legacy Class |
          Thread Safe but Slower]